            <p>Translations And Printing In All Languages	Memorandum. Publication Office The American Hebrew<lb/>
                From<lb/></p>
            <p>Phil. Cowen&#44; Printer&#44;<lb/>
                498&#45;500 Third Avenue&#44;<lb/>
                Telephone&#58; 243 39<hi rend="sup">th</hi>.</p>
                
            <p>New York&#44; 20 April 1884&#44;<lb/>
                To Rev. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Phila Pa<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Dear Mr.  Morais&#58;&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>I am  in receipt of your note of the 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#44; and<lb/> also of Mr. Piza&#39;s letter&#44; and will submit them to the<lb/> Board at the next meeting. Permit me to say however that<lb/> when Mr. Morais expresses an opinion differing from the<lb/> Amer. Hebrew&#44; we accept it as an honest difference of opinion<lb/> and not as a reflection upon the Hebrew&#44; for we have<lb/> not quite attained to infallibility. The question raised is<lb/> one that I am not competent to speak on and will be<lb/> taken care of by the &#34;clerical section&#34; of the board.<lb/></p>
            <p>We have ordered from the publishers Mesrs.<lb/> Houghton&#44; Mifflin &#38; Co. to be sent to you the Life &#38; Letters<lb/> of Jas &#38; Lucretia Mott&#44; and will be pleased<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>to have you write us a review of the book if<lb/> your time will permit. We have taken the liberty<lb/> of doing so because of the personal acquaintance<lb/>with the Motts which we believe you enjoyed.<lb/> I may suggest&#44; that if time presses&#44; it is perfectly<lb/> proper to use the title of the book merely as the<lb/> text&#44; <del>for a brief sketch</del> and instead of reviewing<lb/> the &#34;life &#38; letters&#34;¬ù to give a brief sketch of the persons<lb/> or subject treated. We would prefer a short notice.<lb/> From half a column to a column if possible but leave<lb/> that entirely to yourself.<lb/></p>
            <p>Truly Yrs<lb/>
                P Cowen<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
